                        "displayName": "Antoine Pitrou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "I think we could also rethink the StopSource lifecycle:\r\n\r\n* have StopToken hold a _weak_ pointer to the StopSource\r\n* StopSource must be held by the stopping side for as long as stopping might be desired\r\n* then {{SetSignalStopSource}} can return some kind of {{shared_ptr}} to the same instance, so that it can be called several times\r\n\r\n",
