                        "displayName": "Antoine Pitrou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "By the way, we must keep in mind that signals interrupting a task is not the only use case for which StopSource / StopToken was designed.\r\n\r\nAnother important use case is: when a server starts some long-winded work on behalf of the client, it must be able to cancel the work if the client drops the connection. In this model, each client connection will instantiate a distinct StopSource.",
